54/////// exchange-add operation for atomic operations on reference counters ///////
55#ifdef CV_XADD
56 // allow to use user-defined macro
57#elif defined __GNUC__
58
59 #if defined __clang__ && __clang_major__ >= 3 && !defined __ANDROID__ && !defined __EMSCRIPTEN__ && !defined(__CUDACC__)
60 #ifdef __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST
61 #define CV_XADD(addr, delta) __c11_atomic_fetch_add((_Atomic(int)*)(addr), (delta), __ATOMIC_SEQ_CST)
62 #else
63 #define CV_XADD(addr, delta) __atomic_fetch_add((_Atomic(int)*)(addr), (delta), 5)
64 #endif
65 #elif __GNUC__*10 + __GNUC_MINOR__ >= 42
66
67 #if !(defined WIN32 || defined _WIN32) && (defined __i486__ || defined __i586__ || \
68 defined __i686__ || defined __MMX__ || defined __SSE__ || defined __ppc__) || \
69 defined _STLPORT_MAJOR || defined _LIBCPP_VERSION || \
70 defined __EMSCRIPTEN__
71
72 #define CV_XADD __sync_fetch_and_add
73 #else
74 #include <ext/atomicity.h>
75 #define CV_XADD __gnu_cxx::__exchange_and_add
76 #endif
77
78 #else
79 #include <bits/atomicity.h>
80 #if __GNUC__*10 + __GNUC_MINOR__ >= 34
81 #define CV_XADD __gnu_cxx::__exchange_and_add
82 #else
83 #define CV_XADD __exchange_and_add
84 #endif
85 #endif
86
87#elif defined WIN32 || defined _WIN32 || defined WINCE
88 namespace cv { CV_EXPORTS int _interlockedExchangeAdd(int* addr, int delta); }
89 #define CV_XADD cv::_interlockedExchangeAdd
90
91#else
92 static inline int CV_XADD(int* addr, int delta)
93 { int tmp = *addr; *addr += delta; return tmp; }
94#endif

116/////////////// saturate_cast (used in image & signal processing) ///////////////////
117
118template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(uchar v) { return _Tp(v); }
119template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(schar v) { return _Tp(v); }
120template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(ushort v) { return _Tp(v); }
121template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(short v) { return _Tp(v); }
122template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(unsigned v) { return _Tp(v); }
123template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(int v) { return _Tp(v); }
124template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(float v) { return _Tp(v); }
125template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp saturate_cast(double v) { return _Tp(v); }
126
127template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(schar v)
128{ return (uchar)std::max((int)v, 0); }
129template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(ushort v)
130{ return (uchar)std::min((unsigned)v, (unsigned)UCHAR_MAX); }
131template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(int v)
132{ return (uchar)((unsigned)v <= UCHAR_MAX ? v : v > 0 ? UCHAR_MAX : 0); }
133template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(short v)
134{ return saturate_cast<uchar>((int)v); }
135template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(unsigned v)
136{ return (uchar)std::min(v, (unsigned)UCHAR_MAX); }
137template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(float v)
138{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<uchar>(iv); }
139template<> inline uchar saturate_cast<uchar>(double v)
140{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<uchar>(iv); }
141
142template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(uchar v)
143{ return (schar)std::min((int)v, SCHAR_MAX); }
144template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(ushort v)
145{ return (schar)std::min((unsigned)v, (unsigned)SCHAR_MAX); }
146template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(int v)
147{
148 return (schar)((unsigned)(v-SCHAR_MIN) <= (unsigned)UCHAR_MAX ?
149 v : v > 0 ? SCHAR_MAX : SCHAR_MIN);
150}
151template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(short v)
152{ return saturate_cast<schar>((int)v); }
153template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(unsigned v)
154{ return (schar)std::min(v, (unsigned)SCHAR_MAX); }
155
156template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(float v)
157{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<schar>(iv); }
158template<> inline schar saturate_cast<schar>(double v)
159{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<schar>(iv); }
160
161template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(schar v)
162{ return (ushort)std::max((int)v, 0); }
163template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(short v)
164{ return (ushort)std::max((int)v, 0); }
165template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(int v)
166{ return (ushort)((unsigned)v <= (unsigned)USHRT_MAX ? v : v > 0 ? USHRT_MAX : 0); }
167template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(unsigned v)
168{ return (ushort)std::min(v, (unsigned)USHRT_MAX); }
169template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(float v)
170{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<ushort>(iv); }
171template<> inline ushort saturate_cast<ushort>(double v)
172{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<ushort>(iv); }
173
174template<> inline short saturate_cast<short>(ushort v)
175{ return (short)std::min((int)v, SHRT_MAX); }
176template<> inline short saturate_cast<short>(int v)
177{
178 return (short)((unsigned)(v - SHRT_MIN) <= (unsigned)USHRT_MAX ?
179 v : v > 0 ? SHRT_MAX : SHRT_MIN);
180}
181template<> inline short saturate_cast<short>(unsigned v)
182{ return (short)std::min(v, (unsigned)SHRT_MAX); }
183template<> inline short saturate_cast<short>(float v)
184{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<short>(iv); }
185template<> inline short saturate_cast<short>(double v)
186{ int iv = cvRound(v); return saturate_cast<short>(iv); }
187
188template<> inline int saturate_cast<int>(float v) { return cvRound(v); }
189template<> inline int saturate_cast<int>(double v) { return cvRound(v); }
190
191// we intentionally do not clip negative numbers, to make -1 become 0xffffffff etc.
192template<> inline unsigned saturate_cast<unsigned>(float v){ return cvRound(v); }
193template<> inline unsigned saturate_cast<unsigned>(double v) { return cvRound(v); }
194
195inline int fast_abs(uchar v) { return v; }
196inline int fast_abs(schar v) { return std::abs((int)v); }
197inline int fast_abs(ushort v) { return v; }
198inline int fast_abs(short v) { return std::abs((int)v); }
199inline int fast_abs(int v) { return std::abs(v); }
200inline float fast_abs(float v) { return std::abs(v); }
201inline double fast_abs(double v) { return std::abs(v); }

206template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx()
207{
208 for(int i = 0; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
209}
210
211template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(_Tp v0)
212{
213 val[0] = v0;
214 for(int i = 1; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
215}
216
217template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(_Tp v0, _Tp v1)
218{
219 assert(channels >= 2);
220 val[0] = v0; val[1] = v1;
221 for(int i = 2; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
222}
223
224template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(_Tp v0, _Tp v1, _Tp v2)
225{
226 assert(channels >= 3);
227 val[0] = v0; val[1] = v1; val[2] = v2;
228 for(int i = 3; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
229}
230
231template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(_Tp v0, _Tp v1, _Tp v2, _Tp v3)
232{
233 assert(channels >= 4);
234 val[0] = v0; val[1] = v1; val[2] = v2; val[3] = v3;
235 for(int i = 4; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
236}

240 assert(channels >= 5);
241 val[0] = v0; val[1] = v1; val[2] = v2; val[3] = v3; val[4] = v4;
242 for(int i = 5; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);
243}

245template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(_Tp v0, _Tp v1, _Tp v2, _Tp v3,
246 _Tp v4, _Tp v5)
247{
248 assert(channels >= 6);
249 val[0] = v0; val[1] = v1; val[2] = v2; val[3] = v3;
250 val[4] = v4; val[5] = v5;
251 for(int i = 6; i < channels; i++) val[i] = _Tp(0);

306template<typename _Tp, int m, int n>
307inline Matx<_Tp,m,n>::Matx(_Tp v0, _Tp v1, _Tp v2, _Tp v3,
308 _Tp v4, _Tp v5, _Tp v6, _Tp v7,
309 _Tp v8, _Tp v9, _Tp v10, _Tp v11,

319template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::Matx(const _Tp* values)
320{
321 for( int i = 0; i < channels; i++ ) val[i] = values[i];

324template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline Matx<_Tp, m, n> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::all(_Tp alpha)
325{
326 Matx<_Tp, m, n> M;
327 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ ) M.val[i] = alpha;
328 return M;
329}

331template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
332Matx<_Tp,m,n> Matx<_Tp,m,n>::zeros()
333{
334 return all(0);
335}

337template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
338Matx<_Tp,m,n> Matx<_Tp,m,n>::ones()

340 return all(1);
341}

343template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
344Matx<_Tp,m,n> Matx<_Tp,m,n>::eye()
345{
346 Matx<_Tp,m,n> M;
347 for(int i = 0; i < MIN(m,n); i++)
348 M(i,i) = 1;
349 return M;
350}

352template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline _Tp Matx<_Tp, m, n>::dot(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& M) const
353{
354 _Tp s = 0;
355 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ ) s += val[i]*M.val[i];
356 return s;
357}
358
359
360template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline double Matx<_Tp, m, n>::ddot(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& M) const
361{
362 double s = 0;
363 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ ) s += (double)val[i]*M.val[i];
364 return s;
365}

369template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
370Matx<_Tp,m,n> Matx<_Tp,m,n>::diag(const typename Matx<_Tp,m,n>::diag_type& d)
371{
372 Matx<_Tp,m,n> M;
373 for(int i = 0; i < MIN(m,n); i++)
374 M(i,i) = d(i, 0);
375 return M;
376}

397template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> template<typename T2>
398inline Matx<_Tp, m, n>::operator Matx<T2, m, n>() const
399{
400 Matx<T2, m, n> M;
401 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ ) M.val[i] = saturate_cast<T2>(val[i]);
402 return M;
403}

406template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> template<int m1, int n1> inline
407Matx<_Tp, m1, n1> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::reshape() const
408{
409 CV_DbgAssert(m1*n1 == m*n);
410 return (const Matx<_Tp, m1, n1>&)*this;
411}

414template<typename _Tp, int m, int n>
415template<int m1, int n1> inline
416Matx<_Tp, m1, n1> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::get_minor(int i, int j) const
417{
418 CV_DbgAssert(0 <= i && i+m1 <= m && 0 <= j && j+n1 <= n);
419 Matx<_Tp, m1, n1> s;
420 for( int di = 0; di < m1; di++ )
421 for( int dj = 0; dj < n1; dj++ )
422 s(di, dj) = (*this)(i+di, j+dj);
423 return s;
424}

435template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
436Matx<_Tp, m, 1> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::col(int j) const
437{
438 CV_DbgAssert((unsigned)j < (unsigned)n);
439 Matx<_Tp, m, 1> v;
440 for( int i = 0; i < m; i++ )
441 v.val[i] = val[i*n + j];
442 return v;

449 diag_type d;

488template<typename _Tp1, typename _Tp2, int m, int n> static inline
489Matx<_Tp1, m, n>& operator += (Matx<_Tp1, m, n>& a, const Matx<_Tp2, m, n>& b)
490{
491 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ )
492 a.val[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp1>(a.val[i] + b.val[i]);
493 return a;
494}
495
496
497template<typename _Tp1, typename _Tp2, int m, int n> static inline
498Matx<_Tp1, m, n>& operator -= (Matx<_Tp1, m, n>& a, const Matx<_Tp2, m, n>& b)
499{
500 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ )
501 a.val[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp1>(a.val[i] - b.val[i]);
502 return a;
503}

506template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
507Matx<_Tp,m,n>::Matx(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& a, const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& b, Matx_AddOp)
508{
509 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ )
510 val[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(a.val[i] + b.val[i]);
511}

515Matx<_Tp,m,n>::Matx(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& a, const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& b, Matx_SubOp)

522template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> template<typename _T2> inline

530template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
531Matx<_Tp,m,n>::Matx(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& a, const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& b, Matx_MulOp)
532{
533 for( int i = 0; i < m*n; i++ )
534 val[i] = saturate_cast<_Tp>(a.val[i] * b.val[i]);
535}
536
537
538template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> template<int l> inline
539Matx<_Tp,m,n>::Matx(const Matx<_Tp, m, l>& a, const Matx<_Tp, l, n>& b, Matx_MatMulOp)
540{
541 for( int i = 0; i < m; i++ )
542 for( int j = 0; j < n; j++ )
543 {
544 _Tp s = 0;
545 for( int k = 0; k < l; k++ )
546 s += a(i, k) * b(k, j);
547 val[i*n + j] = s;
548 }
549}

717template<typename _Tp, int m> struct Matx_DetOp
718{
719 double operator ()(const Matx<_Tp, m, m>& a) const
720 {
721 Matx<_Tp, m, m> temp = a;
722 double p = LU(temp.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m, 0, 0, 0);
723 if( p == 0 )
724 return p;
725 for( int i = 0; i < m; i++ )
726 p *= temp(i, i);
727 return 1./p;
728 }
729};
730
731
732template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_DetOp<_Tp, 1>
733{
734 double operator ()(const Matx<_Tp, 1, 1>& a) const
735 {
736 return a(0,0);
737 }
738};
739
740
741template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_DetOp<_Tp, 2>
742{
743 double operator ()(const Matx<_Tp, 2, 2>& a) const
744 {
745 return a(0,0)*a(1,1) - a(0,1)*a(1,0);
746 }
747};
748
749
750template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_DetOp<_Tp, 3>
751{
752 double operator ()(const Matx<_Tp, 3, 3>& a) const
753 {
754 return a(0,0)*(a(1,1)*a(2,2) - a(2,1)*a(1,2)) -
755 a(0,1)*(a(1,0)*a(2,2) - a(2,0)*a(1,2)) +
756 a(0,2)*(a(1,0)*a(2,1) - a(2,0)*a(1,1));
757 }
758};

760template<typename _Tp, int m> static inline
761double determinant(const Matx<_Tp, m, m>& a)
762{
763 return Matx_DetOp<_Tp, m>()(a);
764}

784template<typename _Tp, int m> struct Matx_FastInvOp
785{
786 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, m, m>& a, Matx<_Tp, m, m>& b, int method) const
787 {
788 Matx<_Tp, m, m> temp = a;
789
790 // assume that b is all 0's on input => make it a unity matrix
791 for( int i = 0; i < m; i++ )
792 b(i, i) = (_Tp)1;
793
794 if( method == DECOMP_CHOLESKY )
795 return Cholesky(temp.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m, b.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m);
796
797 return LU(temp.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m, b.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m) != 0;
798 }
799};
800
801
802template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_FastInvOp<_Tp, 2>
803{
804 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, 2, 2>& a, Matx<_Tp, 2, 2>& b, int) const
805 {
806 _Tp d = determinant(a);
807 if( d == 0 )
808 return false;
809 d = 1/d;
810 b(1,1) = a(0,0)*d;
811 b(0,0) = a(1,1)*d;
812 b(0,1) = -a(0,1)*d;
813 b(1,0) = -a(1,0)*d;
814 return true;
815 }
816};
817
818
819template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_FastInvOp<_Tp, 3>
820{
821 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, 3, 3>& a, Matx<_Tp, 3, 3>& b, int) const
822 {
823 _Tp d = (_Tp)determinant(a);
824 if( d == 0 )
825 return false;
826 d = 1/d;
827 b(0,0) = (a(1,1) * a(2,2) - a(1,2) * a(2,1)) * d;
828 b(0,1) = (a(0,2) * a(2,1) - a(0,1) * a(2,2)) * d;
829 b(0,2) = (a(0,1) * a(1,2) - a(0,2) * a(1,1)) * d;
830
831 b(1,0) = (a(1,2) * a(2,0) - a(1,0) * a(2,2)) * d;
832 b(1,1) = (a(0,0) * a(2,2) - a(0,2) * a(2,0)) * d;
833 b(1,2) = (a(0,2) * a(1,0) - a(0,0) * a(1,2)) * d;
834
835 b(2,0) = (a(1,0) * a(2,1) - a(1,1) * a(2,0)) * d;
836 b(2,1) = (a(0,1) * a(2,0) - a(0,0) * a(2,1)) * d;
837 b(2,2) = (a(0,0) * a(1,1) - a(0,1) * a(1,0)) * d;
838 return true;
839 }
840};
841
842
843template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
844Matx<_Tp, n, m> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::inv(int method) const
845{
846 Matx<_Tp, n, m> b;
847 bool ok;
848 if( method == DECOMP_LU || method == DECOMP_CHOLESKY )
849 ok = Matx_FastInvOp<_Tp, m>()(*this, b, method);
850 else
851 {
852 Mat A(*this, false), B(b, false);
853 ok = (invert(A, B, method) != 0);
854 }
855 return ok ? b : Matx<_Tp, n, m>::zeros();
856}

859template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> struct Matx_FastSolveOp
860{
861 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, m, m>& a, const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& b,
862 Matx<_Tp, m, n>& x, int method) const
863 {
864 Matx<_Tp, m, m> temp = a;
865 x = b;
866 if( method == DECOMP_CHOLESKY )
867 return Cholesky(temp.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m, x.val, n*sizeof(_Tp), n);
868
869 return LU(temp.val, m*sizeof(_Tp), m, x.val, n*sizeof(_Tp), n) != 0;
870 }
871};
872
873
874template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_FastSolveOp<_Tp, 2, 1>
875{
876 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, 2, 2>& a, const Matx<_Tp, 2, 1>& b,
877 Matx<_Tp, 2, 1>& x, int) const
878 {
879 _Tp d = determinant(a);
880 if( d == 0 )
881 return false;
882 d = 1/d;
883 x(0) = (b(0)*a(1,1) - b(1)*a(0,1))*d;
884 x(1) = (b(1)*a(0,0) - b(0)*a(1,0))*d;
885 return true;
886 }
887};
888
889
890template<typename _Tp> struct Matx_FastSolveOp<_Tp, 3, 1>
891{
892 bool operator()(const Matx<_Tp, 3, 3>& a, const Matx<_Tp, 3, 1>& b,
893 Matx<_Tp, 3, 1>& x, int) const
894 {
895 _Tp d = (_Tp)determinant(a);
896 if( d == 0 )
897 return false;
898 d = 1/d;
899 x(0) = d*(b(0)*(a(1,1)*a(2,2) - a(1,2)*a(2,1)) -
900 a(0,1)*(b(1)*a(2,2) - a(1,2)*b(2)) +
901 a(0,2)*(b(1)*a(2,1) - a(1,1)*b(2)));
902
903 x(1) = d*(a(0,0)*(b(1)*a(2,2) - a(1,2)*b(2)) -
904 b(0)*(a(1,0)*a(2,2) - a(1,2)*a(2,0)) +
905 a(0,2)*(a(1,0)*b(2) - b(1)*a(2,0)));
906
907 x(2) = d*(a(0,0)*(a(1,1)*b(2) - b(1)*a(2,1)) -
908 a(0,1)*(a(1,0)*b(2) - b(1)*a(2,0)) +
909 b(0)*(a(1,0)*a(2,1) - a(1,1)*a(2,0)));
910 return true;
911 }
912};

915template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> template<int l> inline
916Matx<_Tp, n, l> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::solve(const Matx<_Tp, m, l>& rhs, int method) const
917{
918 Matx<_Tp, n, l> x;
919 bool ok;
920 if( method == DECOMP_LU || method == DECOMP_CHOLESKY )
921 ok = Matx_FastSolveOp<_Tp, m, l>()(*this, rhs, x, method);
922 else
923 {
924 Mat A(*this, false), B(rhs, false), X(x, false);
925 ok = cv::solve(A, B, X, method);
926 }
927
928 return ok ? x : Matx<_Tp, n, l>::zeros();
929}

931template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> inline
932Vec<_Tp, n> Matx<_Tp, m, n>::solve(const Vec<_Tp, m>& rhs, int method) const
933{
934 Matx<_Tp, n, 1> x = solve(reinterpret_cast<const Matx<_Tp, m, 1>&>(rhs), method);
935 return reinterpret_cast<Vec<_Tp, n>&>(x);
936}

938template<typename _Tp, typename _AccTp> static inline
939_AccTp normL2Sqr(const _Tp* a, int n)
940{
941 _AccTp s = 0;
942 int i=0;
943 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
944 for( ; i <= n - 4; i += 4 )
945 {
946 _AccTp v0 = a[i], v1 = a[i+1], v2 = a[i+2], v3 = a[i+3];
947 s += v0*v0 + v1*v1 + v2*v2 + v3*v3;
948 }
949#endif
950 for( ; i < n; i++ )
951 {
952 _AccTp v = a[i];
953 s += v*v;
954 }
955 return s;
956}
957
958
959template<typename _Tp, typename _AccTp> static inline
960_AccTp normL1(const _Tp* a, int n)
961{
962 _AccTp s = 0;
963 int i = 0;
964#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
965 for(; i <= n - 4; i += 4 )
966 {
967 s += (_AccTp)fast_abs(a[i]) + (_AccTp)fast_abs(a[i+1]) +
968 (_AccTp)fast_abs(a[i+2]) + (_AccTp)fast_abs(a[i+3]);
969 }
970#endif
971 for( ; i < n; i++ )
972 s += fast_abs(a[i]);
973 return s;
974}

977template<typename _Tp, typename _AccTp> static inline
978_AccTp normInf(const _Tp* a, int n)
979{
980 _AccTp s = 0;
981 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
982 s = std::max(s, (_AccTp)fast_abs(a[i]));
983 return s;
984}

987template<typename _Tp, typename _AccTp> static inline
988_AccTp normL2Sqr(const _Tp* a, const _Tp* b, int n)
989{
990 _AccTp s = 0;
991 int i= 0;
992#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
993 for(; i <= n - 4; i += 4 )
994 {
995 _AccTp v0 = _AccTp(a[i] - b[i]), v1 = _AccTp(a[i+1] - b[i+1]), v2 = _AccTp(a[i+2] - b[i+2]), v3 = _AccTp(a[i+3] - b[i+3]);
996 s += v0*v0 + v1*v1 + v2*v2 + v3*v3;
997 }
998#endif
999 for( ; i < n; i++ )
1000 {
1001 _AccTp v = _AccTp(a[i] - b[i]);
1002 s += v*v;
1003 }
1004 return s;
1005}

1013template<> inline float normL2Sqr(const float* a, const float* b, int n)
1014{
1015 if( n >= 8 )
1016 return normL2Sqr_(a, b, n);
1017 float s = 0;
1018 for( int i = 0; i < n; i++ )
1019 {
1020 float v = a[i] - b[i];
1021 s += v*v;
1022 }
1023 return s;
1024}

1027template<typename _Tp, typename _AccTp> static inline
1028_AccTp normL1(const _Tp* a, const _Tp* b, int n)
1029{
1030 _AccTp s = 0;
1031 int i= 0;
1032#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1033 for(; i <= n - 4; i += 4 )
1034 {
1035 _AccTp v0 = _AccTp(a[i] - b[i]), v1 = _AccTp(a[i+1] - b[i+1]), v2 = _AccTp(a[i+2] - b[i+2]), v3 = _AccTp(a[i+3] - b[i+3]);
1036 s += std::abs(v0) + std::abs(v1) + std::abs(v2) + std::abs(v3);
1037 }
1038#endif
1039 for( ; i < n; i++ )
1040 {
1041 _AccTp v = _AccTp(a[i] - b[i]);

1043 }
1044 return s;

1085template<typename _Tp, int m, int n> static inline
1086double norm(const Matx<_Tp, m, n>& M, int normType)
1087{
1088 return normType == NORM_INF ? (double)normInf<_Tp, typename DataType<_Tp>::work_type>(M.val, m*n) :
1089 normType == NORM_L1 ? (double)normL1<_Tp, typename DataType<_Tp>::work_type>(M.val, m*n) :
1090 std::sqrt((double)normL2Sqr<_Tp, typename DataType<_Tp>::work_type>(M.val, m*n));
1091}

1928template<typename _Tp> static inline Rect_<_Tp>& operator &= ( Rect_<_Tp>& a, const Rect_<_Tp>& b )
1929{
1930 _Tp x1 = std::max(a.x, b.x), y1 = std::max(a.y, b.y);
1931 a.width = std::min(a.x + a.width, b.x + b.width) - x1;
1932 a.height = std::min(a.y + a.height, b.y + b.height) - y1;
1933 a.x = x1; a.y = y1;
1934 if( a.width <= 0 || a.height <= 0 )
1935 a = Rect();
1936 return a;
1937}

1939template<typename _Tp> static inline Rect_<_Tp>& operator |= ( Rect_<_Tp>& a, const Rect_<_Tp>& b )
1940{
1941 _Tp x1 = std::min(a.x, b.x), y1 = std::min(a.y, b.y);
1942 a.width = std::max(a.x + a.width, b.x + b.width) - x1;
1943 a.height = std::max(a.y + a.height, b.y + b.height) - y1;
1944 a.x = x1; a.y = y1;
1945 return a;
1946}

2265
2266// template vector class. It is similar to STL's vector,
2267// with a few important differences:
2268// 1) it can be created on top of user-allocated data w/o copying it
2269// 2) vector b = a means copying the header,
2270// not the underlying data (use clone() to make a deep copy)
2271template <typename _Tp> class Vector
2272{
2273public:
2274 typedef _Tp value_type;
2275 typedef _Tp* iterator;
2276 typedef const _Tp* const_iterator;
2277 typedef _Tp& reference;
2278 typedef const _Tp& const_reference;
2279
2280 struct Hdr
2281 {
2282 Hdr() : data(0), datastart(0), refcount(0), size(0), capacity(0) {};
2283 _Tp* data;
2284 _Tp* datastart;
2285 int* refcount;
2286 size_t size;
2287 size_t capacity;
2288 };
2289
2290 Vector() {}
2291 Vector(size_t _size) { resize(_size); }
2292 Vector(size_t _size, const _Tp& val)
2293 {
2294 resize(_size);
2295 for(size_t i = 0; i < _size; i++)
2296 hdr.data[i] = val;
2297 }
2298 Vector(_Tp* _data, size_t _size, bool _copyData=false)
2299 { set(_data, _size, _copyData); }
2300
2301 template<int n> Vector(const Vec<_Tp, n>& vec)
2302 { set((_Tp*)&vec.val[0], n, true); }
2303
2304 Vector(const std::vector<_Tp>& vec, bool _copyData=false)
2305 { set(!vec.empty() ? (_Tp*)&vec[0] : 0, vec.size(), _copyData); }
2306
2307 Vector(const Vector& d) { *this = d; }
2308
2309 Vector(const Vector& d, const Range& r_)
2310 {
2311 Range r = r_ == Range::all() ? Range(0, d.size()) : r_;
2312 /*if( r == Range::all() )
2313 r = Range(0, d.size());*/
2314 if( r.size() > 0 && r.start >= 0 && r.end <= d.size() )
2315 {
2316 if( d.hdr.refcount )
2317 CV_XADD(d.hdr.refcount, 1);
2318 hdr.refcount = d.hdr.refcount;
2319 hdr.datastart = d.hdr.datastart;
2320 hdr.data = d.hdr.data + r.start;
2321 hdr.capacity = hdr.size = r.size();
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 Vector<_Tp>& operator = (const Vector& d)
2326 {
2327 if( this != &d )
2328 {
2329 if( d.hdr.refcount )
2330 CV_XADD(d.hdr.refcount, 1);
2331 release();
2332 hdr = d.hdr;
2333 }
2334 return *this;
2335 }
2336
2337 ~Vector() { release(); }
2338
2339 Vector<_Tp> clone() const
2340 { return hdr.data ? Vector<_Tp>(hdr.data, hdr.size, true) : Vector<_Tp>(); }
2341
2342 void copyTo(Vector<_Tp>& vec) const
2343 {
2344 size_t i, sz = size();
2345 vec.resize(sz);
2346 const _Tp* src = hdr.data;
2347 _Tp* dst = vec.hdr.data;
2348 for( i = 0; i < sz; i++ )
2349 dst[i] = src[i];
2350 }
2351
2352 void copyTo(std::vector<_Tp>& vec) const
2353 {
2354 size_t i, sz = size();
2355 vec.resize(sz);
2356 const _Tp* src = hdr.data;
2357 _Tp* dst = sz ? &vec[0] : 0;
2358 for( i = 0; i < sz; i++ )
2359 dst[i] = src[i];
2360 }
2361
2362 operator CvMat() const
2363 { return cvMat((int)size(), 1, type(), (void*)hdr.data); }
2364
2365 _Tp& operator [] (size_t i) { CV_DbgAssert( i < size() ); return hdr.data[i]; }
2366 const _Tp& operator [] (size_t i) const { CV_DbgAssert( i < size() ); return hdr.data[i]; }
2367 Vector operator() (const Range& r) const { return Vector(*this, r); }
2368 _Tp& back() { CV_DbgAssert(!empty()); return hdr.data[hdr.size-1]; }
2369 const _Tp& back() const { CV_DbgAssert(!empty()); return hdr.data[hdr.size-1]; }
2370 _Tp& front() { CV_DbgAssert(!empty()); return hdr.data[0]; }
2371 const _Tp& front() const { CV_DbgAssert(!empty()); return hdr.data[0]; }
2372
2373 _Tp* begin() { return hdr.data; }
2374 _Tp* end() { return hdr.data + hdr.size; }
2375 const _Tp* begin() const { return hdr.data; }
2376 const _Tp* end() const { return hdr.data + hdr.size; }
2377
2378 void addref() { if( hdr.refcount ) CV_XADD(hdr.refcount, 1); }
2379 void release()
2380 {
2381 if( hdr.refcount && CV_XADD(hdr.refcount, -1) == 1 )
2382 {
2383 delete[] hdr.datastart;
2384 delete hdr.refcount;
2385 }
2386 hdr = Hdr();
2387 }
2388
2389 void set(_Tp* _data, size_t _size, bool _copyData=false)
2390 {
2391 if( !_copyData )
2392 {
2393 release();
2394 hdr.data = hdr.datastart = _data;
2395 hdr.size = hdr.capacity = _size;
2396 hdr.refcount = 0;
2397 }
2398 else
2399 {
2400 reserve(_size);
2401 for( size_t i = 0; i < _size; i++ )
2402 hdr.data[i] = _data[i];
2403 hdr.size = _size;
2404 }
2405 }
2406
2407 void reserve(size_t newCapacity)
2408 {
2409 _Tp* newData;
2410 int* newRefcount;
2411 size_t i, oldSize = hdr.size;
2412 if( (!hdr.refcount || *hdr.refcount == 1) && hdr.capacity >= newCapacity )
2413 return;
2414 newCapacity = std::max(newCapacity, oldSize);
2415 newData = new _Tp[newCapacity];
2416 newRefcount = new int(1);
2417 for( i = 0; i < oldSize; i++ )
2418 newData[i] = hdr.data[i];
2419 release();
2420 hdr.data = hdr.datastart = newData;
2421 hdr.capacity = newCapacity;
2422 hdr.size = oldSize;
2423 hdr.refcount = newRefcount;
2424 }
2425
2426 void resize(size_t newSize)
2427 {
2428 size_t i;
2429 newSize = std::max(newSize, (size_t)0);
2430 if( (!hdr.refcount || *hdr.refcount == 1) && hdr.size == newSize )
2431 return;
2432 if( newSize > hdr.capacity )
2433 reserve(std::max(newSize, std::max((size_t)4, hdr.capacity*2)));
2434 for( i = hdr.size; i < newSize; i++ )
2435 hdr.data[i] = _Tp();
2436 hdr.size = newSize;
2437 }
2438
2439 Vector<_Tp>& push_back(const _Tp& elem)
2440 {
2441 if( hdr.size == hdr.capacity )
2442 reserve( std::max((size_t)4, hdr.capacity*2) );
2443 hdr.data[hdr.size++] = elem;
2444 return *this;
2445 }
2446
2447 Vector<_Tp>& pop_back()
2448 {
2449 if( hdr.size > 0 )
2450 --hdr.size;
2451 return *this;
2452 }
2453
2454 size_t size() const { return hdr.size; }
2455 size_t capacity() const { return hdr.capacity; }
2456 bool empty() const { return hdr.size == 0; }
2457 void clear() { resize(0); }
2458 int type() const { return DataType<_Tp>::type; }
2459
2460protected:
2461 Hdr hdr;
2462};

2465template<typename _Tp> inline typename DataType<_Tp>::work_type
2466dot(const Vector<_Tp>& v1, const Vector<_Tp>& v2)
2467{
2468 typedef typename DataType<_Tp>::work_type _Tw;
2469 size_t i = 0, n = v1.size();
2470 assert(v1.size() == v2.size());
2471
2472 _Tw s = 0;
2473 const _Tp *ptr1 = &v1[0], *ptr2 = &v2[0];
2474 for( ; i < n; i++ )
2475 s += (_Tw)ptr1[i]*ptr2[i];
2476
2477 return s;
2478}

2975template<typename _Tp> static inline FileStorage& operator << (FileStorage& fs, const _Tp& value)
2976{
2977 if( !fs.isOpened() )
2978 return fs;
2979 if( fs.state == FileStorage::NAME_EXPECTED + FileStorage::INSIDE_MAP )
2980 CV_Error( CV_StsError, "No element name has been given" );
2981 write( fs, fs.elname, value );
2982 if( fs.state & FileStorage::INSIDE_MAP )
2983 fs.state = FileStorage::NAME_EXPECTED + FileStorage::INSIDE_MAP;
2984 return fs;
2985}

3161template<typename _Tp, int numflag> class VecReaderProxy
3162{
3163public:
3164 VecReaderProxy( FileNodeIterator* _it ) : it(_it) {}
3165 void operator()(vector<_Tp>& vec, size_t count) const
3166 {
3167 count = std::min(count, it->remaining);
3168 vec.resize(count);
3169 for( size_t i = 0; i < count; i++, ++(*it) )
3170 read(**it, vec[i], _Tp());
3171 }
3172 FileNodeIterator* it;
3173};
3174
3175template<typename _Tp> class VecReaderProxy<_Tp,1>
3176{
3177public:
3178 VecReaderProxy( FileNodeIterator* _it ) : it(_it) {}
3179 void operator()(vector<_Tp>& vec, size_t count) const
3180 {
3181 size_t remaining = it->remaining, cn = DataType<_Tp>::channels;
3182 int _fmt = DataType<_Tp>::fmt;
3183 char fmt[] = { (char)((_fmt>>8)+'1'), (char)_fmt, '\0' };
3184 size_t remaining1 = remaining/cn;
3185 count = count < remaining1 ? count : remaining1;
3186 vec.resize(count);
3187 it->readRaw( string(fmt), !vec.empty() ? (uchar*)&vec[0] : 0, count*sizeof(_Tp) );
3188 }
3189 FileNodeIterator* it;
3190};

3194{
3195 VecReaderProxy<_Tp, DataType<_Tp>::fmt != 0> r(&it);
3196 r(vec, maxCount);
3197}

3274template<typename _Tp> static inline _Tp gcd(_Tp a, _Tp b)
3275{
3276 if( a < b )
3277 std::swap(a, b);
3278 while( b > 0 )
3279 {
3280 _Tp r = a % b;
3281 a = b;
3282 b = r;
3283 }
3284 return a;
3285}

3327template<typename _Tp, class _LT> void sort( vector<_Tp>& vec, _LT LT=_LT() )
3328{
3329 int isort_thresh = 7;
3330 int sp = 0;
3331
3332 struct
3333 {
3334 _Tp *lb;
3335 _Tp *ub;
3336 } stack[48];
3337
3338 size_t total = vec.size();
3339
3340 if( total <= 1 )
3341 return;
3342
3343 _Tp* arr = &vec[0];
3344 stack[0].lb = arr;
3345 stack[0].ub = arr + (total - 1);
3346
3347 while( sp >= 0 )
3348 {
3349 _Tp* left = stack[sp].lb;
3350 _Tp* right = stack[sp--].ub;
3351
3352 for(;;)
3353 {
3354 int i, n = (int)(right - left) + 1, m;
3355 _Tp* ptr;
3356 _Tp* ptr2;
3357
3358 if( n <= isort_thresh )
3359 {
3360 insert_sort:
3361 for( ptr = left + 1; ptr <= right; ptr++ )
3362 {
3363 for( ptr2 = ptr; ptr2 > left && LT(ptr2[0],ptr2[-1]); ptr2--)
3364 std::swap( ptr2[0], ptr2[-1] );
3365 }
3366 break;
3367 }
3368 else
3369 {
3370 _Tp* left0;
3371 _Tp* left1;
3372 _Tp* right0;
3373 _Tp* right1;
3374 _Tp* pivot;
3375 _Tp* a;
3376 _Tp* b;
3377 _Tp* c;
3378 int swap_cnt = 0;
3379
3380 left0 = left;
3381 right0 = right;
3382 pivot = left + (n/2);
3383
3384 if( n > 40 )
3385 {
3386 int d = n / 8;
3387 a = left, b = left + d, c = left + 2*d;
3388 left = LT(*a, *b) ? (LT(*b, *c) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? c : a))
3389 : (LT(*c, *b) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? a : c));
3390
3391 a = pivot - d, b = pivot, c = pivot + d;
3392 pivot = LT(*a, *b) ? (LT(*b, *c) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? c : a))
3393 : (LT(*c, *b) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? a : c));
3394
3395 a = right - 2*d, b = right - d, c = right;
3396 right = LT(*a, *b) ? (LT(*b, *c) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? c : a))
3397 : (LT(*c, *b) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? a : c));
3398 }
3399
3400 a = left, b = pivot, c = right;
3401 pivot = LT(*a, *b) ? (LT(*b, *c) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? c : a))
3402 : (LT(*c, *b) ? b : (LT(*a, *c) ? a : c));
3403 if( pivot != left0 )
3404 {
3405 std::swap( *pivot, *left0 );
3406 pivot = left0;
3407 }
3408 left = left1 = left0 + 1;
3409 right = right1 = right0;
3410
3411 for(;;)
3412 {
3413 while( left <= right && !LT(*pivot, *left) )
3414 {
3415 if( !LT(*left, *pivot) )
3416 {
3417 if( left > left1 )
3418 std::swap( *left1, *left );
3419 swap_cnt = 1;
3420 left1++;
3421 }
3422 left++;
3423 }
3424
3425 while( left <= right && !LT(*right, *pivot) )
3426 {
3427 if( !LT(*pivot, *right) )
3428 {
3429 if( right < right1 )
3430 std::swap( *right1, *right );
3431 swap_cnt = 1;
3432 right1--;
3433 }
3434 right--;
3435 }
3436
3437 if( left > right )
3438 break;
3439 std::swap( *left, *right );
3440 swap_cnt = 1;
3441 left++;
3442 right--;
3443 }
3444
3445 if( swap_cnt == 0 )
3446 {
3447 left = left0, right = right0;
3448 goto insert_sort;
3449 }
3450
3451 n = std::min( (int)(left1 - left0), (int)(left - left1) );
3452 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
3453 std::swap( left0[i], left[i-n] );
3454
3455 n = std::min( (int)(right0 - right1), (int)(right1 - right) );
3456 for( i = 0; i < n; i++ )
3457 std::swap( left[i], right0[i-n+1] );
3458 n = (int)(left - left1);
3459 m = (int)(right1 - right);
3460 if( n > 1 )
3461 {
3462 if( m > 1 )
3463 {
3464 if( n > m )
3465 {
3466 stack[++sp].lb = left0;
3467 stack[sp].ub = left0 + n - 1;
3468 left = right0 - m + 1, right = right0;
3469 }
3470 else
3471 {
3472 stack[++sp].lb = right0 - m + 1;
3473 stack[sp].ub = right0;
3474 left = left0, right = left0 + n - 1;
3475 }
3476 }
3477 else
3478 left = left0, right = left0 + n - 1;
3479 }
3480 else if( m > 1 )
3481 left = right0 - m + 1, right = right0;
3482 else
3483 break;
3484 }
3485 }
3486 }
3487}

3518// This function splits the input sequence or set into one or more equivalence classes and
3519// returns the vector of labels - 0-based class indexes for each element.
3520// predicate(a,b) returns true if the two sequence elements certainly belong to the same class.
3521//
3522// The algorithm is described in "Introduction to Algorithms"
3523// by Cormen, Leiserson and Rivest, the chapter "Data structures for disjoint sets"
3524template<typename _Tp, class _EqPredicate> int
3525partition( const vector<_Tp>& _vec, vector<int>& labels,
3526 _EqPredicate predicate=_EqPredicate())
3527{
3528 int i, j, N = (int)_vec.size();
3529 const _Tp* vec = &_vec[0];
3530
3531 const int PARENT=0;
3532 const int RANK=1;
3533
3534 vector<int> _nodes(N*2);
3535 int (*nodes)[2] = (int(*)[2])&_nodes[0];
3536
3537 // The first O(N) pass: create N single-vertex trees
3538 for(i = 0; i < N; i++)
3539 {
3540 nodes[i][PARENT]=-1;
3541 nodes[i][RANK] = 0;
3542 }
3543
3544 // The main O(N^2) pass: merge connected components
3545 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
3546 {
3547 int root = i;
3548
3549 // find root
3550 while( nodes[root][PARENT] >= 0 )
3551 root = nodes[root][PARENT];
3552
3553 for( j = 0; j < N; j++ )
3554 {
3555 if( i == j || !predicate(vec[i], vec[j]))
3556 continue;
3557 int root2 = j;
3558
3559 while( nodes[root2][PARENT] >= 0 )
3560 root2 = nodes[root2][PARENT];
3561
3562 if( root2 != root )
3563 {
3564 // unite both trees
3565 int rank = nodes[root][RANK], rank2 = nodes[root2][RANK];
3566 if( rank > rank2 )
3567 nodes[root2][PARENT] = root;
3568 else
3569 {
3570 nodes[root][PARENT] = root2;
3571 nodes[root2][RANK] += rank == rank2;
3572 root = root2;
3573 }
3574 assert( nodes[root][PARENT] < 0 );
3575
3576 int k = j, parent;
3577
3578 // compress the path from node2 to root
3579 while( (parent = nodes[k][PARENT]) >= 0 )
3580 {
3581 nodes[k][PARENT] = root;
3582 k = parent;
3583 }
3584
3585 // compress the path from node to root
3586 k = i;
3587 while( (parent = nodes[k][PARENT]) >= 0 )
3588 {
3589 nodes[k][PARENT] = root;
3590 k = parent;
3591 }
3592 }
3593 }
3594 }
3595
3596 // Final O(N) pass: enumerate classes
3597 labels.resize(N);
3598 int nclasses = 0;
3599
3600 for( i = 0; i < N; i++ )
3601 {
3602 int root = i;
3603 while( nodes[root][PARENT] >= 0 )
3604 root = nodes[root][PARENT];
3605 // re-use the rank as the class label
3606 if( nodes[root][RANK] >= 0 )
3607 nodes[root][RANK] = ~nclasses++;
3608 labels[i] = ~nodes[root][RANK];
3609 }
3610
3611 return nclasses;
3612}

3820#if defined(__QNX__)
3821 // No long std::abs(long) in QNX
3822 long absdelta = (delta < 0) ? -delta : delta;
3823 if( absdelta > n )
3824#else
3825 if( std::abs(static_cast<long>(delta)) > n )
3826#endif
3827 delta += delta < 0 ? n : -n;
3828
3829 return delta;
3830}

3952/** \brief prints Mat to the output stream allows in the specified notation (see format)
3953 * use like
3954 @verbatim
3955 Mat my_mat = Mat::eye(3,3,CV_32F);

3957 @endverbatim
3958 */
